  135 HttpClient
  136 should be used. It also does not handle cookies at the moment.
  137 Using the Web Client
  138 To use Vert.x Web Client, add the following dependency to the
  139 dependencies
  140 section of your build descriptor:
  141 Maven (in your
  142 pom.xml
  143 ):
  144 <dependency>
  145 <groupId>
  146 io.vertx
  147 </groupId>
  148 <artifactId>
  149 vertx-web-client
  150 </artifactId>
  151 <version>
  152 5.1.3
  153 </version>
  154 </dependency>
  155 Gradle (in your
  156 build.gradle
  157 file):
  158 dependencies {
  159 compile
  160 '
  161 io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.1.3
  162 '
  163 }
  164 Re-cap on Vert.x core HTTP client
  165 Vert.x Web Client uses the API from Vert.x core, so it’s well worth getting familiar with the basic concepts of using
  166 HttpClient
  167 using Vert.x core, if you’re not already.
  168 Creating a Web Client
  169 You create an
  170 WebClient
  171 instance with default options as follows
  172 WebClient
  173 client
  174 =
  175 WebClient
  176 .
  177 create
  178 (
  179 vertx
  180 )
  181 ;
  182 If you want to configure options for the client, you create it as follows
  183 WebClientOptions
  184 options
  185 =
  186 new
  187 WebClientOptions
  188 ()
  189 .
