sory info. It appears I should focus on having a single JSON configuration.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker image is needed for normal Vert.x Web Client coverage, but native-image runs for 5.0.1 still need the Netty unsafe-access runtime system properties on JDK 25.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set native test runtime/system properties for the generated tests: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 resolves through vertx-core:5.0.1 to Netty 4.2.2.Final, and the existing 5.0.0 test already documents the same Netty 4.2.x Java 25 native-run requirement but gates it only on libraryVersion == '5.0.0'. Meaningful coverage can use an in-process Vert.x HttpServer plus WebClient/WebClientSession/CachingWebClient; no external service is normally required. Avoid OAuth2WebClient coverage unless intentionally adding the optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 dependency.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If the generated build keeps the existing version-specific guard, GVM_TCK_LV=5.0.1 will skip the Netty runtime properties and can reproduce the native-image run failure.\",\n    \"OAuth2WebClient references optional OAuth2 types; tests that import that API without adding io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 will fail to compile.\",\n    \"Vert.x clients, servers, files, and Vertx instances must be closed in tests to avoid hanging event-loop resources.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a48974aadab31e9016a40f3c50b808190a00381cdcddbf748\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2605, "output": 654, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33979, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782641596425, "responseId": "